Toyota Accepts Japan Labor Union’s Request to Raise Pay, Bonuses

-- B y   M a s a t s u g u   H o r i e   a n d   N a o k o   F u j i m u r a
-- 
2011-03-16T04:40:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/toyota-accepts-japan-labor-union-s-request-to-raise-pay-bonuses.html
  Toyota Motor Corp. (7203) , the world’s
largest automaker, accepted its Japanese labor union’s request
for wage and bonus increases.  The Toyota City, Japan-based company will raise average
worker pay by 87,600 yen ($1,083) a year and give bonuses of
1.81 million yen, the automaker said in a statement today. The
Toyota Motor Workers’ Union asked the company to increase wages
and bonuses in February as part of annual negotiations.  Toyota shares gained 7.1 percent to 3,280 yen as of 1:15
p.m. in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Masatsugu Horie in Osaka at 
